        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I was mistaken, there is no issue with the grammar structure here.\r\nI have spent some time to check this issue again, this time I wiped out both old runtime files of nvim and any plugins then installed nvim from source again.\r\n\r\nRegardless of the changes there I made to the grammar there was no difference in highlighting. :sweat_smile: \r\n\r\nIf I understand what happened correctly, it goes like this:\r\n- all contents of `codeblock` are highlighted with `@text.literal` - this is correct\r\n- injected parser parses the contents of the `codeblock` and highlights some nodes accordingly to its highlights queries - this is also correct\r\n- nodes that are not highlighted by injected parser will inherit `codeblock` color, even though in regular file they would be displayed with `Normal` highlight\r\n\r\nIf the range handled by injected parser would be highlighted with `Normal` the final highlights would be the same as in regular file. I will search for issues/discussions about it and try to come up with some solution.\r\n\r\nI am closing this issue because this has nothing to do with grammar. ",
