            "body": "Colorscheme is okay - checked that with built-in [retrobox](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/runtime/colors/retrobox.vim). It's more likely the context that matters.\r\n\r\nLet's say I have defined only the following highlights queries for C:\r\n```scm\r\n((identifier) @variable)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen I would end up with those highlights in C file:\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/tree-sitter-vimdoc/assets/88032359/82074a2a-4638-44b7-adad-b392bd57ce71)\r\nand those highlights in help file:\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/tree-sitter-vimdoc/assets/88032359/de9cc7d2-8edf-4c86-83c4-ef547c7b7157)\r\n\r\nInjected highlights work fine, but the `Normal` highlight color for injected highlights becomes whatever it paints on. :)\r\n",
